value.0: This aged stone monument seems littered with inscriptions and names though it's meaning is difficult for a lay-person to make out.

Value.value: This monument commemorates the fall of House Arundel and the sons and daughters that lived in the pristine paradise of Aljana. There are many carvings of names, presumably of those that died in the Duskwood. An inscription in old Alzhedo seems to lay the blame for a flood that killed more than a hundred people on a nameless Druid.
